    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="shell">
    <TestimonialsBlock />

    <SimoneCallout />

    <CustomerSegmentBlock />

    <MechanismExplanation />

    <WorkloadFitTable />

    <section class="in-progress">
      <h2>In progress: ReadonlyREST's own build catalog → Hetzner</h2>

      <p>
        Sample so far: a 1.69.0 plugin version compressed <strong>88.5×</strong>
        (2,866 MB → 32.4 MB), bit-perfect SHA-256 round-trip through the
        proxy. About <strong>$9 in EC2 compute</strong> and ~$2 in
        Glacier Bulk-tier retrieval for the migration so far.
      </p>

      <p>
        The full migration covers 145 versions, 8 years of release
        history. Final results published as a reproducible case study
        when complete.
      </p>

      <p>
        → <a href="/case-studies/readonlyrest-builds">Methodology, sample numbers, raw data</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="architecture">
      <h2>How it fits in your stack</h2>

      <p>
        DeltaGlider is an S3-compatible proxy. Your apps speak SigV4 to
        it. It speaks SigV4 to your bucket. On PUT, it stores either an
        xdelta3 delta against the deltaspace reference or a passthrough
        copy, whichever is smaller. On GET, it reconstructs byte-for-byte
        and streams. The client sees ordinary S3.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="operator-surface">
      <h2>Beyond compression — the operator surface</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>
          Per-user S3 credentials, ABAC permissions (AWS-IAM grammar via
          <code>iam-rs</code>), OAuth/OIDC group mapping, encrypted
          SQLCipher config DB.
        </li>
        <li>
          Replication rules between buckets/backends — run-now,
          pause/resume, history, optional delete-replication.
        </li>
        <li>
          AES-256-GCM at-rest encryption, per-object IV. Encryption key
          stays in your runtime; the backend sees ciphertext.
        </li>
        <li>
          Lifecycle expiration, event outbox with retries/webhooks, soft
          per-bucket quotas (including <code>quota=0</code> freeze for
          migration windows), Prometheus metrics, in-memory audit ring
          plus structured stdout for SIEM shipping.
        </li>
        <li>
          Delta efficiency diagnostic panel — one-click scan flags
          prefixes where the reference baseline produces wasted bytes.
        </li>
        <li>
          Pre-auth admission chain — <code>deny</code>/<code>reject</code>/
          <code>allow-anonymous</code> rules evaluated BEFORE auth.
          <code>config trace</code> shows exactly which rule fired and
          why.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>→ <a href="/docs/reference">Reference docs</a></p>
    </section>

